# Explicit domain-level redirects to the primary domain. Netlify can also
# do this automatically via "Primary domain" in Domain management, but
# that wasn't taking effect for these two domain aliases, so it's spelled
# out here instead. The trailing "!" forces the redirect even if a
# matching file exists, which is what we want for a whole-domain redirect.
https://bringyourbills.com.au/*  https://bringyourbills.org.au/:splat  301!
https://bringyourbills.au/*      https://bringyourbills.org.au/:splat  301!

# The publish directory is the repo root, so server-side source and config
# would otherwise be fetchable as static files. These contain no secrets
# (only process.env references), but there's no reason to serve them —
# shadow them with a 404 so the internal structure isn't handed out.
# (The Netlify Functions themselves are invoked at /.netlify/functions/*,
# which is separate from the /netlify/ source path blocked here.)
/netlify/*     /404.html   404
/supabase/*    /404.html   404
/package.json  /404.html   404
/package-lock.json  /404.html   404
